    "created_at": "2017-01-04T12:37:47Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-01-04T12:46:53Z",
    "body": "The fastest way (from what I can tell) is to Stringify the Object in the main thread:\r\n``` javascript\r\nglobal.myStringifiedLargeObject = JSON.stringify(myLargeObject);\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou can then access this in the renderer using:\r\n``` javascript\r\nimport { remote } from 'electron'\r\n\r\nconst myLargeObject = JSON.parse(remote.getGlobal('myStringifiedLargeObject'))\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Speed Comparison:\r\nI've tried all three methods on an approx 200kB object.\r\n* Method 1: JSON.parse(JSON.stringify()) with getGlobal - Approx **800ms**\r\n* Method 2: Writing the JSON to disk and then reading it - Read takes **400ms**\r\n* Method 3: As described above - This takes just under **10ms**"
